<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB0BFD338CCAFBB2FAD5" pageId="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFD338CCAFBB2FAD5" blockId="9.[707,1194,1203,1729]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD338CCAFCB5FB18" bold="true" box="[731,836,1257,1278]" pageId="9">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguishable from the superficially similar 
<taxonomicName id="4C719CFCFFABAB0BFC528D20FBD3FAFE" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[954,1058,1283,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wappesi">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFC528D20FBD3FAFE" box="[954,1058,1283,1304]" italics="true" pageId="9">P. wappesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the small subseriate punctures on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFABAB08FD338D1BFEB9FF14" lastPageId="10" pageId="9" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFABAB0BFD338D1BFB64F927" blockId="9.[707,1194,1203,1729]" pageId="9">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD338D1BFC64FAAB" bold="true" box="[731,917,1336,1357]" pageId="9">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 8.0 mm; width 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFABAB0BFD2B8D70FCEBFA8E" box="[707,794,1363,1384]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFCC08D70FC94FA8E" bold="true" box="[808,869,1363,1384]" pageId="9">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFC568D70FBE0FA8E" box="[958,1041,1363,1384]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="21.[197,237,1489,1508]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,194,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-75@21.[172,1193,192,1465]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs. 92–97. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 92) P. helvinus; 93) P. maracayensis; 94) P. modestus; 95) P. bilineatus;" pageId="9">Fig. 95</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFBC88D70FB50FA8E" bold="true" box="[1056,1185,1363,1384]" pageId="9">Integument</emphasis>
: Cranium and most of pronotum yellow-brown, pronotum infuscated at base; elytra mostly yellow-brown, disc and epipleural margin with faint yellow line; femora mostly yellow, profemur infuscated distally; tibiae light brown; pterothorax and abdomen brown. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFC478DD1FC16F9E1" bold="true" box="[943,999,1522,1543]" pageId="9">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes wider than frons (24:14); funicular antennomeres moderately expanded, 6 
<superScript id="7C044A37FFABAB0BFCD68E01FCBDF9D6" attach="left" box="[830,844,1570,1584]" fontSize="6" pageId="9">th</superScript>
antennomere not large (
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFBA78E0BFB6FF9DB" box="[1103,1182,1576,1597]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[175,216,1487,1506]" captionTargetBox="[167,1170,207,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[151,1172,183,1487]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 21–38. Pujoliclerus species, antennae. 21) P. helvinus; 22) P. maracayensis; 23) P. bilineatus; 24) P. calceatus; 25) P. corumba; 26) P. ovatus; 27) P. wappesi; 28) P. amplus; 29) P. flavoapicalus; 30) P. gilvus; 31) P. hermani; 32) P. alajuela; 33) P. orellana; 34) P. megacavus; 35) P. oxinus; 36) P. alboordinus; 37) P. apolegmus; 38) P. catarina." pageId="9">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFD2B8E61FCE3F9B1" bold="true" box="[707,786,1602,1623]" pageId="9">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum transverse (55:48), lateral tubercle very prominent (
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFC548E7EFBF6F994" box="[956,1031,1629,1650]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[175,215,1395,1414]" captionTargetBox="[151,1155,183,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-114@18.[151,1172,183,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 48–61. Pujoliclerus species, pronota. 48) P. helvinus; 49) P. maracayensis; 50) P. modestus; 51) P. bilineatus; 52) P. calceatus; 53) P. corumba; 54) P. flavolimbatus; 55) P. ovatus; 56) P. wappesi; 57) P. amplus; 58) P. flavoapicalus; 59) P. gilvus; 60) P. hermani; 61) P. orellana." pageId="9">Fig. 51</figureCitation>
); epipleural fold gradually narrowed to elytral apex, asetiferous punctures prominent to elytral apex. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFABAB0BFBD68EB1FB52F941" bold="true" box="[1086,1187,1682,1703]" pageId="9">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Tegminal lobes and phallic apex as in 
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFABAB0BFBAF8E8FFB60F927" box="[1095,1169,1708,1729]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="20.[175,215,1170,1189]" captionTargetBox="[164,629,189,1147]" captionTargetId="figure-461@20.[151,638,183,1159]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs. 76–91. Pujoliclerus species, aedeagi. 76) P. helvinus; 77) P. bilineatus; 78) P. calceatus; 79) P. corumba; 80) P. flavolimbatus; 81) P. ovatus (tegmen only); 82) P. wappesi; 83) P. gilvus; 84) P. hermani; 85) P. casselorum; 86) P. catarina (phallus only); 87) P. argus; 88) P. aspigalbus; 89) P. flora; 90) P. posticalis; 91) P. pallidus." pageId="9">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF4788E1FEB9FF14" blockId="10.[151,639,194,348]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF4788E1FEA6FF31" bold="true" box="[175,343,194,215]" pageId="10">Natural History.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54CA59DDFFA8AB08FE7C88E1FE1AFF31" box="[404,491,194,215]" pageId="10">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected during November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFA8AB08FF4788D4FD8EFEEA" box="[175,639,247,268]" pageId="10" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF4788D4FD8EFEEA" blockId="10.[151,639,194,348]" box="[175,639,247,268]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF4788D4FEDCFEEA" bold="true" box="[175,301,247,268]" pageId="10">Distribution.</emphasis>
Known only from 
<collectingCountry id="F366A7EFFFA8AB08FE0B88D4FDE8FEEA" box="[483,537,247,268]" name="Brazil" pageId="10">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFA8AB08FDCD88D4FD85FEEA" box="[549,628,247,268]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="26.[709,741,859,878]" captionTargetBox="[206,1171,184,835]" captionTargetId="figure-18@26.[685,1172,183,836]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="Fig. 123. Geographic distribution of six Pujoliclerus species." pageId="10">Fig. 123</figureCitation>
