</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFA8AB08FF478931FDFDFE5A" pageId="10" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF478931FE93FEBA" blockId="10.[151,639,194,348]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF478931FED3FEC1" bold="true" box="[175,290,274,295]" pageId="10">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet stems from 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF7F890FFF19FEA7" box="[151,232,300,321]" italics="true" pageId="10">bilineata</emphasis>
, a Latin name that refers to the two yellow lines on each elytron.
