<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFA8AB08FF478C37FEEFFB9E" pageId="10" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF478C37FEEFFB9E" blockId="10.[151,638,1044,1729]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF478C37FEE9FBCF" bold="true" box="[175,280,1044,1065]" pageId="10">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The arenose condition of the elytral interstitial spaces will distinguish the members of this species from superficially similar specimens of 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF5B8C40FEEFFB9E" box="[179,286,1123,1144]" italics="true" pageId="10">
<taxonomicName id="4C719CFCFFA8AB08FF5B8C40FEEBFB9E" authorityName="Opitz" authorityYear="2014" box="[179,282,1123,1144]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Pujoliclerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wappesi">P. wappesi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36BB4F4FFA8AB08FF478C5CFE37F927" pageId="10" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF478C5CFDA6F9B1" blockId="10.[151,638,1044,1729]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF478C5CFE96FB72" bold="true" box="[175,359,1151,1172]" pageId="10">Description. Size</emphasis>
: Length 6.0 mm; width 2.0 mm. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF188CBAFED9FB48" bold="true" box="[240,296,1177,1198]" pageId="10">Form</emphasis>
: As in 
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFA8AB08FE9D8CBAFE4CFB48" box="[373,445,1177,1198]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="21.[197,237,1489,1508]" captionTargetBox="[173,1193,194,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-75@21.[172,1193,192,1465]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs. 92–97. Pujoliclerus species, habitus. 92) P. helvinus; 93) P. maracayensis; 94) P. modestus; 95) P. bilineatus;" pageId="10">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FE208CBAFDCCFB48" bold="true" box="[456,573,1177,1198]" pageId="10">Integument</emphasis>
: Head mostly reddish brown, lower frons and epicranium narrowly black, antenna black; pronotum mostly reddish brown, black at disc and lower sides; elytral disc mostly reddish brown, apical region and sutural margin brown, epipleural margin brown near humerus; femora mostly yellow, infuscated distally, tibiae brown; pterothorax, and abdomen black. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF0A8D4DFEEBFA65" bold="true" box="[226,282,1390,1411]" pageId="10">Head</emphasis>
: Eyes as wide as frons (13:13); funicular antennomeres considerably expanded, 6 
<superScript id="7C044A37FFA8AB08FF4C8DBEFF43FA4D" attach="left" box="[164,178,1437,1451]" fontSize="6" pageId="10">th</superScript>
antennomere not acuminate, capitulum particularly long (
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFA8AB08FEC88D9EFE97FA34" box="[288,358,1469,1490]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="8.[175,216,1487,1506]" captionTargetBox="[167,1170,207,1464]" captionTargetId="figure-1@8.[151,1172,183,1487]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figs. 21–38. Pujoliclerus species, antennae. 21) P. helvinus; 22) P. maracayensis; 23) P. bilineatus; 24) P. calceatus; 25) P. corumba; 26) P. ovatus; 27) P. wappesi; 28) P. amplus; 29) P. flavoapicalus; 30) P. gilvus; 31) P. hermani; 32) P. alajuela; 33) P. orellana; 34) P. megacavus; 35) P. oxinus; 36) P. alboordinus; 37) P. apolegmus; 38) P. catarina." pageId="10">Fig. 24</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FE9F8D9EFE31FA34" bold="true" box="[375,448,1469,1490]" pageId="10">Thorax</emphasis>
: Pronotum quadrate (50:50), lateral tubercle moderately prominent (
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFA8AB08FF768DD1FF12F9E1" box="[158,227,1522,1543]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="18.[175,215,1395,1414]" captionTargetBox="[151,1155,183,1382]" captionTargetId="figure-114@18.[151,1172,183,1383]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Figs. 48–61. Pujoliclerus species, pronota. 48) P. helvinus; 49) P. maracayensis; 50) P. modestus; 51) P. bilineatus; 52) P. calceatus; 53) P. corumba; 54) P. flavolimbatus; 55) P. ovatus; 56) P. wappesi; 57) P. amplus; 58) P. flavoapicalus; 59) P. gilvus; 60) P. hermani; 61) P. orellana." pageId="10">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
); asetiferous punctures widespread on elytral disc, interstitial spaces arenose, epipleural fold wide, gradually diminishing to elytral apex. 
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FDFB8E0BFD86F9DB" bold="true" box="[531,631,1576,1597]" pageId="10">Abdomen</emphasis>
: Tegminal lobes and phallic apex as in 
<figureCitation id="134AFBFAFFA8AB08FDE38E61FDA3F9B1" box="[523,594,1602,1623]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="20.[175,215,1170,1189]" captionTargetBox="[164,629,189,1147]" captionTargetId="figure-461@20.[151,638,183,1159]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Figs. 76–91. Pujoliclerus species, aedeagi. 76) P. helvinus; 77) P. bilineatus; 78) P. calceatus; 79) P. corumba; 80) P. flavolimbatus; 81) P. ovatus (tegmen only); 82) P. wappesi; 83) P. gilvus; 84) P. hermani; 85) P. casselorum; 86) P. catarina (phallus only); 87) P. argus; 88) P. aspigalbus; 89) P. flora; 90) P. posticalis; 91) P. pallidus." pageId="10">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF478E7EFD96F96A" blockId="10.[151,638,1044,1729]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF478E7EFEBDF994" bold="true" box="[175,332,1629,1650]" pageId="10">Variation. Size</emphasis>
: Length 6.0– 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFA8AB08FE088E7EFDC5F994" box="[480,564,1629,1650]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="7.5">7.5 mm</quantity>
; width 2.0– 
<quantity id="4C894A9AFFA8AB08FF298E54FEE0F96A" box="[193,273,1655,1676]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" pageId="10" unit="mm" value="2.2">2.2 mm</quantity>
. The elytra may be entirely black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCEE77FFFA8AB08FF478EB1FE37F927" blockId="10.[151,638,1044,1729]" pageId="10">
<emphasis id="B9053B6DFFA8AB08FF478EB1FEA6F941" bold="true" box="[175,343,1682,1703]" pageId="10">Natural History.</emphasis>
Specimens were collected during October and November.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
